	                                <p>Just a note to anyone using the symfony upgrade fixer, it doesn't always detect and fix 'text, entity, date, choice' form-field types.</p><p>It also has a habit of changing the use statement order of files that its not touched in any way. So if you have a touchy tech-lead and your using VCS it'll look  like you've touched more files than you have.</p><p>This is just a note to suggest that the tools isn't followed blindly.</p><p>These issues have been noted to the author on the git repo.</p>
